.","pos":[74525,74702]},{"content":"Create Layoutmodification.xml.","pos":[74708,74738]},{"content":"Note: It is recommended to start with the sample on USB-B\\StartLayout\\layoutModification.xml as it conforms to the samples in this document (example only).","pos":[74744,74899]},{"content":"The Sample LayoutModification.xml shows two groups called “Fabrikam Group 1\" and “Fabrikam Group 2”, which contain tiles that will be applied if the device country/region matches what’s specified in Region (in this case, the regions are Germany and United States).","pos":[74905,75169]},{"content":"Each group contains three tiles and the various elements you need to use depending on the tile that you want to pin to Start.","pos":[75170,75295]},{"content":"Keep the following in mind when creating your LayoutModification.xml file:","pos":[75301,75375]},{"pos":[75385,75627],"content":"If you are pinning a Classic Windows application using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>start:DesktopApplicationTile<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tag and you don’t know the application’s application user model ID, you need to create a .lnk file in a legacy Start Menu directory before first boot."},{"pos":[75637,75826],"content":"If you use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>start:DesktopApplicationTile<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tag to pin a legacy .url shortcut to Start, you must create a .url file and add this file to a legacy Start Menu directory before first boot."},{"content":"For those scenarios, you can use the following directories to put the .url or .lnk files:","pos":[75832,75921]},{"content":"%APPDATA%\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\","pos":[75931,75979]},{"content":"%ALLUSERSPROFILE%\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\","pos":[75989,76045]},{"content":"Save the LayoutModification.xml file.","pos":[76051,76088]},{"content":"Add your LayoutModification.xml file to the Windows image.","pos":[76094,76152]},{"content":"You’ll need to put the file in the following specific location before first boot