 id=\"p2\">***</bpt>diskpart<ept id=\"p2\">***</ept> and press <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;lt;</ph>Enter<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> to start Diskpart."},{"pos":[84535,84597],"content":"At the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>\\DISKPART<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> command line, type <bpt id=\"p2\">***</bpt>list volume<ept id=\"p2\">***</ept>."},{"pos":[84603,84736],"content":"Under the “<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Label”<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> column, identify the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> drive and note the letter of the volume under the “<bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>Ltr”<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> column (for example, E)."},{"pos":[84742,84775],"content":"Type <bpt id=\"p1\">***</bpt>exit<ept id=\"p1\">***</ept> to quit Diskpart."},{"content":"Deploy the image","pos":[84782,84798]},{"pos":[84800,84940],"content":"Using the deployment script walkthrough-deploy.bat in <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>/Deployment folder, lay out the partitions on the device and apply the image."},{"content":"Important: The Recovery partition must be the partition after the Windows partition to ensure winre.wim can be kept up-to-date during life of the device.","pos":[84945,85098]},{"content":"In Windows 10 Version 1511, we are changing our recommendation to have the WinRE partition placed after the OS partition.","pos":[85102,85223]},{"content":"This allows future growth of the WinRE partition during updates.","pos":[85224,85288]},{"content":"Today with the WinRE partition at the front of the disk, the size of it can never be changed, making it difficult to update WinRE when needed.","pos":[85289,85431]},{"content":"We will continue to support having the WinRE partition located in different parts of the disk, but we encourage you to follow the new recommendation.","pos":[85432,85581]},{"content":"There are several pauses in the script.","pos":[85655,85694]},{"content":"You will be prompted Y/N for the Apply operation if this is a Compact OS deployment.","pos":[85695,85779]},{"content":"Note: Only use Compact OS on Flash drive based devices because Compact OS performance depends heavily on the storage device capabilities.","pos":[85781,85918]},{"content":"Compact OS is NOT recommended on rotational devices.","pos":[85919,85971]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Compact OS<ept id=\"p1\">](compact-os.md)</ept>.","pos":[85972,86026]},{"content":"After the computer boots to the OOBE screen, press this key combination to boot into Audit mode:","pos":[86028,86124]},{"content":"Preload Microsoft Office","pos":[86149,86173]},{"content":"This section provides guidance for pre-loading Office 2016 and Office v15.4.","pos":[86175,86251]},{"content":"Preload Microsoft Office 2016","pos":[86258,86287]},{"content":"This guide provides information for licensed original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) about how to use the Office Deployment Tool to preinstall Office 2016 on to devices that are running the Windows operating system.","pos":[86289,86504]},{"content":"Note: This guide doesn’t cover the PIPC scenarios for OEMs in Japan.","pos":[86506,86574]},{"content":"Prepare Office files on Technician PC","pos":[86583,86620]},{"content":"Obtain Office Deployment Tool from X20-92403 Office 2016 v16 Deployment tool for OEM OPK.","pos":[86622,86711]},{"content":"Mount X20-92403 Office 2016 v16 Deployment Tool for OEM OPK\\Software - DVD\\X20-92404 SW DVD5 Office 2016 v16 Deployment Tool for OEM\\x20-92404.img.","pos":[86717,86864]},{"content":"Copy files from mounted drive to USB-B (where E:\\ is driver letter for USB-B) E:\\OfficeV16.","pos":[86869,86960]},{"content":"Double click e:\\Officev16\\officedeploymenttool.exe.","pos":[86965,87016]},{"content":"Provide folder path to extract files E:\\Officev16.","pos":[87021,87071]},{"content":"Setup.exe and configuration.xml are extracted to E:\\Officev16.","pos":[87077,87139]},{"content":"Setup and configuration.xml","pos":[87147,87174]},{"content":"Obtain Office v16 in the desired language; this sample uses English X20-39283 Office 2016 v16 32-BIT X64 English OPK.","pos":[87220,87337]},{"content":"Copy the folder Office from mounted drive X20-39283 Office 2016 v16 32-BIT X64 English OPK\\Software - DVD\\X20-37728 SW DVD5 Office Pro 2016 32 64 English C2ROPK Pro HS HB OEM\\X20-37728.img to USB-B (where E:\\ is drive letter for USB-B) E:\\OfficeV16.","pos":[87346,87595]},{"content":"Office folder","pos":[87603,87616]},{"content":"[Optional] If you applied a language interface pack, you may want to add the language interface pack for Office 2016 as well.","pos":[87653,87778]},{"content":"The below samples will show with the Language interface pack applied.","pos":[87779,87848]},{"content":"Notepad E:\\Officev16\\ConfigureO365Home.xml","pos":[87857,87899]},{"content":"Add language ID and verify SourcePath as in the following screenshot.","pos":[87904,87973]},{"content":"Language ID","pos":[87981,87992]},{"content":"Close and save ConfigureO365Home.xml.","pos":[88026,88063]},{"content":"Open an elevated command prompt as administrator.","pos":[88068,88117]},{"content":"From E:\\Officev16, type and run setup.exe /download ConfigureO365Home.xml:","pos":[88123,88197]},{"pos":[88203,88264],"content":"CD E:\\Officev16 Setup.exe /download ConfigureO365Home.xml","leadings":["","    "]},{"content":"This will download the language packs for German and Japanese.","pos":[88274,88336]},{"content":"Type and run echo %errorlevel% and verify return code is 0.","pos":[88346,88405]},{"content":"Unplug USB-B from the technician computer.","pos":[88411,88453]},{"content":"Install Office 2016 on Reference PC","pos":[88462,88497]},{"content":"Plug USB-B into the reference computer, which is in Audit mode.","pos":[88502,88565]},{"content":"Find the drive letter for USB-B; for this example USB-B is E:","pos":[88570,88631]},{"content":"Notepad ConfigureO365Home.xml.","pos":[88638,88668]},{"content":"Configure the SourcePath to point to USB-B E:\\Officev16.","pos":[88673,88729]},{"content":"Configure the source path","pos":[88737,88762]},{"content":"Note: the only Product ID that needs to be specified in the configuration.xml file is O365HomePremRetail.","pos":[88807,88912]},{"content":"If the user enters a key for another product, such as for Office Home &amp; Student 2016, then Office will automatically be configured as the product associated with that key.","pos":[88913,89084]},{"content":"Close and Save ConfigureO365Home.xml.","pos":[89094,89131]},{"content":"Open a command prompt and navigate to d:\\Officev16.","pos":[89136,89187]},{"content":"Type:","pos":[89192,89197]},{"content":"Setup.exe /configure ConfigureO365Home.xml","pos":[89203,89245]},{"content":"Pin Office tiles to the Start menu","pos":[89253,89287]},{"content":"You must pin the Office tiles to the Start menu, otherwise Windows will remove the Office files during OOBE boot phase.","pos":[89289,89408]},{"content":"Note: You must be using at least version 10.0.10586.0 of Windows 10.","pos":[89410,89478]},{"content":"The following steps don’t work with earlier versions of Windows 10.","pos":[89479,89546]},{"content":"Open a command prompt and type:","pos":[89551,89582]},{"content":"Add <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>AppendOfficeSuiteChoice Choice=\"Desktop2016\" /<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> to layoutmodification as you see highlighted in the following example:","pos":[89691,89820]},{"content":"Layout Modification","pos":[89828,89847]},{"content":"Note: The Choice attribute is new.","pos":[89885,89919]},{"content":"This allows different versions of Office to be pinned to the Start screen at the same time.","pos":[89920,90011]},{"content":"For now, Desktop2016 is the only valid value.","pos":[90012,90057]},{"content":"Other values will be available in the future.","pos":[90058,90103]},{"content":"Close and save layoutmodification.xml.","pos":[90108,90146]},{"content":"Note: for recovery purposes the layoutmodification.xml will need to be copied during recovery.","pos":[90152,90246]},{"content":"Open a command prompt and type:","pos":[90257,90288]},{"content":"Once the machine is booted to desktop after going through OOBE, the Start menu will have these three tiles appended as shown in the following diagram:","pos":[90405,90555]},{"content":"Office tiles pinned to the Start menu","pos":[90568,90605]},{"content":"Configure the Setup experience for the user","pos":[90665,90708]},{"content":"After you install Office on the device, you also need to configure the Setup experience for the user.","pos":[90713,90814]},{"content":"This is the experience the user sees when they open an Office app for the first time on the device.","pos":[90815,90914]},{"content":"This also is intended to ensure that Office is properly licensed and activated.","pos":[90915,90994]},{"content":"Setup mode","pos":[91000,91010]},{"content":"Description","pos":[91014,91025]},{"content":"OEM","pos":[91068,91071]},{"content":"In this mode, a customer can choose to try, buy, or activate Office with an existing account, PIN, or product key.","pos":[91082,91196]},{"content":"This mode doesn’t support Activation for Office (AFO) or AFO late binding.","pos":[91197,91271]},{"content":"Therefore, if you choose this mode, you need to provide the customer with an Activation Card (formerly called a product key card or a Microsoft Product Identifier (MPI) card).","pos":[91272,91447]},{"content":"OEMTA","pos":[91454,91459]},{"content":"This mode supports the try, buy, or activate experience of the OEM mode as well as supporting AFO and AFO late binding.","pos":[91470,91589]},{"content":"This mode supports Office activation through the device’s Windows product key, which means the customer wouldn’t need to enter a 5x5 product key code.","pos":[91590,91740]},{"content":"OEM Mode – Provide user with activation card","pos":[91745,91789]},{"content":"In command prompt go to drive letter for USB-B\\Officev16","pos":[91794,91850]},{"content":"Type and run:","pos":[91855,91868]},{"content":"oemsetup.cmd Mode=OEM","pos":[91875,91896]},{"content":"OEMTA Mode – Activation is done through the device’s Windows product key.","pos":[91898,91971]},{"content":"Type and run:","pos":[91976,91989]},{"content":"oemsetup.cmd Mode=OEMTA Referral=","pos":[91996,92029]},{"content":"Preload Microsoft Office Single Image v15.4","pos":[92040,92083]},{"content":"The current preload method of Office 2013 is different from other desktop apps.","pos":[92085,92164]},{"content":"OEMs preinstall desktop apps so the apps are installed.","pos":[92165,92220]},{"content":"This means that when the user launches the app, the app is already installed and automatically opens with no additional installation tasks other than EULA acceptance and/or user registration.","pos":[92221,92412]},{"content":"With Office, compressed setup files are copied to the disk in addition to an out-of-box experience (OOBE) application which captures Office file associations and gives users an entry point to Try, Buy or Activate Office.","pos":[92413,92633]},{"content":"Users do not have access to Word or Excel on the Start screen or in the All Apps view until they launch Office OOBE which is typically made available as a tile on the Start screen.","pos":[92634,92814]},{"content":"When the user launches Office OOBE, setup of Office begins.","pos":[92815,92874]},{"content":"Once Office setup is complete, the compressed setup files that are no longer necessary are removed from the disk.","pos":[92875,92988]},{"content":"Pre-install Office single image (either with or without perpetual or subscription license) or Office Mobile.","pos":[92994,93102]},{"content":"Office Mobile must be used on devices with screen size of 10.1\" and below, and Office single image must be used on devices with screen sizes above 10.1\".","pos":[93104,93257]},{"content":"For devices that have a single fixed storage drive with less than 32 GB, OEMs may preinstall Office Mobile, regardless of the screen size.","pos":[93258,93396]},{"content":"OEMs must have only one Office image on the customer system at a time.","pos":[93397,93467]},{"content":"Pin Office tiles to the Start Menu in such slots that are visible without scrolling, regardless of OEM Systems’ Start Menu layout, unless the Office Tiles or Office tile, as applicable, are pinned as part of the Microsoft Group of Start Menu tiles.","pos":[93473,93721]},{"content":"Obtain: Office Single Image  OPK for language of your region.","pos":[93723,93784]},{"content":"For this document, we will use en-us OPK for sample OPK X19-96440 Office 2013 Single Image v15.4 english OPK.","pos":[93785,93894]},{"content":"This is the latest Office OPK when this guide is published.","pos":[93896,93955]},{"content":"Please verify on SOC (<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>https://www.microsoftoem.com<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.microsoftoem.com)</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> Software  Order Center) if a newer version of Office Single Image OPK exists.","pos":[93956,94121]},{"content":"Note: If Office Tiles are automatically pinned as part of the Microsoft Group of Start Menu tiles, skip the entire following section about tile replacement.","pos":[94123,94279]},{"content":"For Office single image v15, pin the Office tile as medium sized tile or larger.","pos":[94285,94365]},{"content":"For Office Mobile or Office single image v15 successor, pin 3 Office tiles (Word, Excel, PowerPoint tiles) as small sized tiles or larger in a 2x2 orientation.","pos":[94371,94530]},{"content":"Windows 8, 8.1","pos":[94742,94792]},{"content":"Windows 10","pos":[94878,94924]},{"content":"Single Image","pos":[95037,95085]},{"content":"Version 15 = 1 tile","pos":[95171,95226]},{"content":"Next version = 3 tiles","pos":[95252,95310]},{"content":"Version 15 = 1 tile","pos":[95396,95451]},{"content":"Next version = 3 tiles","pos":[95477,95535]},{"content":"Office \"universal\" apps","pos":[95648,95707]},{"content":"N/A","pos":[95793,95832]},{"content":"3 tiles","pos":[95918,95961]},{"content":"3 tiles pinning examples","pos":[96022,96046]},{"content":"4 tiles","pos":[96069,96076]},{"content":"3 tiles","pos":[96111,96118]},{"content":"1 tile pinning example","pos":[96154,96176]},{"content":"1 tile","pos":[96180,96186]},{"content":"Multiple language versions of Office Single Image v15.4 OPK may be preloaded.","pos":[96222,96299]},{"content":"Download all the Microsoft Office Single Image v15.4 OPK languages which are relevant to the languages added to Windows image.","pos":[96300,96426]},{"content":"For example, if English and French language packs are added to Windows image please download:","pos":[96427,96520]},{"pos":[96530,96586],"content":"Office 2013 32 64-bit Single Image v15.4 <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>English<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> OPK"},{"pos":[96596,96651],"content":"Office 2013 32 64-bit Single Image v15.4 <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>French<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> OPK"},{"content":"Note: When different languages of Office get installed consecutively, each additional Office having the different language will occupy ~300MB of disk space instead of ~1GB.","pos":[96657,96829]},{"content":"For example, when Office15 English and Office15 French get installed, total disk space required will be ~1.3GB instead of ~2GB.","pos":[96830,96957]},{"content":"Open an elevated command prompt (with administrative permissions).","pos":[96963,97029]},{"content":"Copy the content of the OPK to a directory, which will be the OfficeSingleImagev15.4 InstallationDirectory.","pos":[97035,97142]},{"content":"Navigate to the installation directory.","pos":[97148,97187]},{"content":"The installation directory is the folder that contains the files shown in the following figure:","pos":[97188,97283]},{"content":"For example: Cd C:<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&amp;</ph>lt;OfficeSingleImagev15.4 InstallationDirectory","pos":[97337,97404]},{"content":"Note: The installation process for the OPK is the same for computers that run 32-bit operating systems or 64-bit operating systems.","pos":[97414,97545]},{"content":"The 32-bit version of Office 2013 may be preloaded on computers that run either 32-bit or 64-bit operating systems.","pos":[97546,97661]},{"content":"The 64-bit version of Office 2013 can be preloaded only on computers that run 64-bit operating systems.","pos":[97662,97765]},{"content":"To prevent possible compatibility issues with add-ins or third-party applications, preload <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>only the 32-bit version<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> of Office Single Image on both 32-bit and 64-bit computers.","pos":[97766,97942]},{"content":"Start the installation by running the office installation script.","pos":[97948,98013]},{"content":"Office Single image install:","pos":[98019,98047]},{"content":"Office Single image install with AFO (Activation for Office)","pos":[98081,98141]},{"content":"After the process is completed, the Microsoft Office application tile will be placed on the Start screen.","pos":[98176,98281]},{"content":"However, the user can install only one language version of Office Single Image v15.4.","pos":[98282,98367]},{"content":"By default, the language version of the OOBE application matches the Windows language settings and the Office Single Image v15.1 language that is preloaded on the computer.","pos":[98368,98540]},{"content":"If this match doesn’t take place, the language dialog box will contain languages that are based on the Office 2013 preloaded languages.","pos":[98541,98676]},{"content":"Prepare system for recovery push-button reset scenarios","pos":[98682,98737]},{"content":"Push-button reset, first introduced in Windows 8, is a built-in recovery tool that allows users to recover the OS while preserving their data and important customizations, without having to back-up their data in advance.","pos":[98739,98959]},{"content":"It reduces the need for custom recovery applications by providing users with more recovery options and the ability to fix their own PCs with confidence.","pos":[98960,99112]},{"content":"In Windows 10, the Push-button reset features have been updated to include the following improvements:","pos":[99114,99216]},{"content":"Image-less recovery","pos":[99224,99243]},{"content":"Push-button reset features no longer require or support a separate recovery image on a local partition or on media.","pos":[99251,99366]},{"content":"This significantly reduces the disk space needed to support the features, and makes recovery possible even on devices with limited storage capacity.","pos":[99367,99515]},{"content":"Recovers to an updated state","pos":[99523,99551]},{"content":"Push-button reset features now recover the Operating System (OS) and drivers (including device applets that are installed as part of INF-based driver packages) to an updated state.","pos":[99555,99735]},{"content":"This reduces the amount of time users have to spend reinstalling the OS updates and drivers after performing a recovery.","pos":[99736,99856]},{"content":"The Push-button reset user experience continues to offer customization opportunities.","pos":[99858,99943]},{"content":"Manufacturers can insert custom scripts, install applications or preserve additional data at available extensibility points.","pos":[99944,100068]},{"content":"The following Push-button reset features are available to users with Windows 10 PCs:","pos":[100070,100154]},{"content":"Refresh your PC","pos":[100162,100177]},{"content":"Fixes software problems by reinstalling the OS while preserving the user data, user accounts, and important settings.","pos":[100185,100302]},{"content":"All other preinstalled customizations are restored to their factory state.","pos":[100303,100377]},{"content":"In Windows 10, this feature no longer preserves user-acquired Universal Windows apps1.","pos":[100378,100464]},{"content":"Reset your PC","pos":[100472,100485]},{"content":"Prepares the PC for recycling or for transfer of ownership by reinstalling the OS, removing all user accounts and contents (e.g. data, Classic Windows applications, and Universal Windows apps), and restoring preinstalled customizations to their factory state.","pos":[100493,100752]},{"content":"Bare metal recovery","pos":[100760,100779]},{"content":"Restores the default or preconfigured partition layout on the system disk, and reinstalls the OS and preinstalled customizations from external media.","pos":[100787,100936]},{"content":"For more information, see:","pos":[100938,100964]},{"content":"Push-button reset","pos":[100968,100985]},{"content":"Windows Recovery Environment (Windows RE)","pos":[101021,101062]},{"content":"Hard Drives and Partitions","pos":[101133,101159]},{"content":"Prepare ScanState tool","pos":[101198,101220]},{"content":"Prepare ScanState tool to capture Classic Windows applications after they have been installed and additional settings like registry.","pos":[101223,101355]},{"content":"Note: You will do this on the technician system.","pos":[101357,101405]},{"content":"On Technician PC, Insert USB-B.","pos":[101411,101442]},{"pos":[101448,101487],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x64<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"pos":[101801,101840],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x86<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"content":"Where E: is the USB-B drive letter.","pos":[102140,102175]},{"content":"Create ScanState configuration file","pos":[102182,102217]},{"content":"OEM can use a configuration file to restore and exclude registry keys and files during the PBR process.","pos":[102219,102322]},{"content":"Important: this section includes a workaround for a known issue in Windows 10.","pos":[102326,102404]},{"content":"You must apply this workaround to avoid issues with the PBR process.","pos":[102405,102473]},{"content":"In some instances, Windows Defender settings and detection history might be captured into the customizations package by the ScanState tool.","pos":[102478,102617]},{"content":"This can lead to failures during recovery due to file conflicts, and causes the PC to reboot and enter the “Installing Windows” phase repeatedly.","pos":[102618,102763]},{"content":"Note: You may use the sample configuration file on USB-B\\Recovery\\recoveryimage\\pbr_config.xml, which covers the steps below.","pos":[102765,102890]},{"pos":[102896,102965],"content":"Use the ScanState tool on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>reference PC running in Audit mode<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."},{"pos":[102971,103010],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x64<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"pos":[103141,103180],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x86<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"content":"Open the configuration file in notepad","pos":[103311,103349]},{"content":"Search for the following lines in the configuration file:","pos":[103403,103460]},{"content":"component displayname=\"Windows-Defender-AM-Sigs\" migrate=\"yes\"…","pos":[103470,103533]},{"content":"component displayname=\"Windows-Defender-AM-Engine\" migrate=\"yes\"…","pos":[103543,103608]},{"content":"component displayname=\"Security-Malware-Windows-Defender\" migrate=\"yes\"…","pos":[103618,103690]},{"content":"Modify the \"migrate\" value from \"yes\" to \"no\" for each line.","pos":[103696,103756]},{"content":"For example:","pos":[103757,103769]},{"pos":[103779,103845],"content":"component displayname=\"Windows-Defender-AM-Sigs\" migrate=\"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>no<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\"…"},{"pos":[103855,103923],"content":"component displayname=\"Windows-Defender-AM-Engine\" migrate=\"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>no<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\"…"},{"pos":[103933,104008],"content":"component displayname=\"Security-Malware-Windows-Defender\" migrate=\"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>no<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\"…"},{"content":"Create ScanState migration file","pos":[104015,104046]},{"content":"OEM may use a configuration file to restore registry keys and files.","pos":[104048,104116]},{"content":"Create a migration XML file used to restore registry values manually entered during manufacturing process.","pos":[104118,104224]},{"content":"The sample below restores the OEMID registry value set earlier in this document.","pos":[104225,104305]},{"content":"Note: USB-B\\recovery\\recoveryimage\\regrecover.xml sample already contains the registry values.","pos":[104307,104401]},{"content":"Create recovery package using ScanState","pos":[104909,104948]},{"content":"Use the ScanState tool to capture the installed customizations into a provisioning package, and save it in the folder c:\\Recovery\\customizations.","pos":[104950,105095]},{"content":"This document uses the samples from <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\\Recovery\\RecoveryImage to create the scanstate package.","pos":[105096,105197]},{"content":"Important: The ScanState package used by PBR must be a .ppkg file stored in C:\\Recovery\\Customizations folder or PBR will not be able to restore the package.","pos":[105199,105356]},{"pos":[105362,105451],"content":"Create the recovery OEM folder and copy the contents of <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\\Recovery\\RecoveryImage."},{"content":"Run ScanState to gather app and customizations.","pos":[105581,105628]},{"pos":[105633,105672],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x64<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"pos":[105682,105927],"content":"'''syntax Mkdir c:\\recovery\\customizations E:\\ScanState_amd64\\scanstate.exe /apps /ppkg C:\\Recovery\\Customizations\\apps.ppkg /i:c:\\recovery\\oem\\regrecover.xml /config:C:\\Recovery\\OEM\\pbr_config.xml /o /c /v:13 /l:C:\\ScanState.log '''","leadings":["","    ","    ","    "]},{"pos":[105936,105975],"content":"If you use an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x86<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Windows 10 image:"},{"pos":[105985,106228],"content":"'''syntax Mkdir c:\\recovery\\customizations E:\\ScanState_x86\\scanstate.exe /apps /ppkg C:\\Recovery\\Customizations\\apps.ppkg /i:c:\\recovery\\oem\\regrecover.xml /config:C:\\Recovery\\OEM\\pbr_config.xml /o /c /v:13 /l:C:\\ScanState.log '''","leadings":["","    ","    ","    "]},{"pos":[106237,106278],"content":"Where E: is the drive letter of <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"},{"content":"Create extensibility scripts to restore additional settings","pos":[106286,106345]},{"content":"You can customize the Push-button reset experience by configuring extensibility points.","pos":[106347,106434]},{"content":"This enables you to run custom scripts, install additional applications, or preserve additional user, application, or registry data.","pos":[106435,106567]},{"content":"The sample script EnableCustomizations.cmd will be called during PBR and will do two things:","pos":[106569,106661]},{"content":"Copy the unattend.xml file used for initial deployment to the \\windows\\panther folder.","pos":[106667,106753]},{"content":"Copy the layoutmodification.xml to the system.","pos":[106759,106805]},{"content":"This will restore the additional layout settings from these two answer files during PBR.","pos":[106807,106895]},{"content":"Important: Recovery scripts and unattend.xml must be copied to c:\\Recovery\\OEM folder for PBR to pickup and restore correctly.","pos":[106899,107025]},{"content":"Copy unattend.xml files for restoring settings.","pos":[107029,107076]},{"content":"For OA 3.0 systems:","pos":[107078,107097]},{"content":"For non-OA 3.0 systems:","pos":[107206,107229]},{"pos":[107341,107363],"content":"where E:\\ is <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"},{"content":"Copy winre.wim backup","pos":[107370,107391]},{"content":"During the deployment the winre.wim file is moved.","pos":[107393,107443]},{"content":"Before capturing the final image the backup winre.wim created in section 4.5.17 must be copied back otherwise the recovery environment will not work on the final image deployment.","pos":[107444,107623]},{"content":"Finalize and capture the manufacturing image","pos":[107702,107746]},{"content":"Delete installation folders and files that have been created of the preloaded applications which are for example, <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>C:\\Office-SingleImagev15.4-Setup<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.","pos":[107752,107901]},{"content":"Existence of these folders may increase the size of .wim file when the image of Windows drive gets captured.","pos":[107902,108010]},{"content":"If the SysPrep Tool is open, close it and open a command prompt as an Administrator.","pos":[108016,108100]},{"content":"Generalize the image by using answerfile with additional settings.","pos":[108106,108172]},{"pos":[108178,108302],"content":"'''syntax C:\\Windows\\System32\\Sysprep\\sysprep /unattend:c:\\recovery\\oem\\Unattend.xml /generalize /oobe /shutdown '''","leadings":["","    ","    "]},{"pos":[108308,108360],"content":"Connect \"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-A<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>\" and boot the Reference computer."},{"pos":[108366,108413],"content":"After WinPE has been booted, connect <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USB-B<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."},{"content":"Troubleshoot: The reference system was shutdown.","pos":[108419,108467]},{"content":"While turning on, if the system continues to boot from Internal HDD, Windows will enter the specialize pass and then the OOBE pass.","pos":[108468,108599]},{"content":"In order to capture a generalized and stable image, none of the Windows passes must be completed.","pos":[108600,108697]},{"content":"To fix this, we need to generalize the image again, and at the OOBE screen, press <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>Ctrl<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;+&amp;lt;</ph>Shift<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;+&amp;lt;</ph>F3<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>.","pos":[108698,108818]},{"content":"The system restarts and boots in Audit mode.","pos":[108819,108863]},{"content":"In Audit mode, Sysprep the system by using the OOBE Shutdown and Generalize switches, as explained previously.","pos":[108864,108974]},{"content":"After the system reboots, make sure to boot from USB-A to WinPE.","pos":[108975,109039]},{"content":"If the system still boots with internal HDD, please make sure USB boot is prioritized instead of HDD boot.","pos":[109046,109152]},{"content":"To do so, it may be necessary to enter the Reference Computer BIOS menu and adjust the boot priority order so that the USB Key is at the top of the list.","pos":[109153,109306]},{"content":"Identify Windows Partition Drive letter.","pos":[109312,109352]},{"pos":[109362,109479],"content":"At the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>X:\\windows\\system32<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> prompt, type <bpt id=\"p2\">***</bpt>diskpart<ept id=\"p2\">***</ept> and press the <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;lt;</ph>Enter<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> key to start Diskpart."},{"pos":[109489,109544],"content":"At the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>\\DISKPART<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> prompt type <bpt id=\"p2\">***</bpt>list volume<ept id=\"p2\">***</ept>."},{"content":"Under the “Label” column, locate the volume that is labeled “Windows”.","pos":[109554,109624]},{"content":"Note what letter it is has been assigned under the “Ltr” column (Example: C).","pos":[109634,109711]},{"content":"This is the drive letter that needs to be used.","pos":[109712,109759]},{"pos":[109769,109802],"content":"Type <bpt id=\"p1\">***</bpt>exit<ept id=\"p1\">***</ept> to quit Diskpart."},{"content":"Diskpart","pos":[109814,109822]},{"content":"[Compact OS limited storage devices only] Convert installed customizations","pos":[109863,109937]},{"content":"Only do this step if you are deploying to limited storage device.","pos":[109939,110004]},{"content":"Single instance will impact the launch performance of some desktop applications.","pos":[110005,110085]},{"pos":[110087,110153],"content":"Please reference <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Compact OS<ept id=\"p1\">](compact-os.md)</ept> for more information."},{"content":"Reduce size of the manufacturing image","pos":[110278,110316]},{"content":"After t